comment:
I always wondered about her snide, under her breath type of comments.  
When my mom was alive, we used to watch her together.  The dancing Ellen, at the show's beginning was our favorite part.
It yanked on my heart when kind things were done for those in need...but it wasn't always her idea or money, right?  She would say how something went viral & the people from the video ended up as guests...Cheerios, Shutterfly & other companies sponsoring her show made the payouts for the advertising time, right?  
My mother wouldn't go to bed without watching DAVID LETTERMAN!  She loved how long his fingers looked on her 52" TV screen & the beautiful colors and designs of his ties.  She thought his honesty & sarcasm were GREAT!
I LOVED HOW HE PAID HIS STAFF DURING A STRIKE OR SOMETHING.  That changed my opinion about him forever and ever.
Why didn't Ellen?   Currently, their networth's are $30 million apart.
Be kind after this...learn from this mess.
I feel bad that she did what she did.
I don't feel bad she is landing where she's landing.
How can you not want to protect other's from the unkind ways of cruel people?
Hopefully she will rethink her ways & NOT make excuses for behavior(s).
Signed,
Never quite a full fan...
